#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:3
msgid "Parallax"
msgstr "Paralaksa"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:5
msgid "**James Lindenschmidt**"
msgstr "**James Lindenschmidt**"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:7
msgid ""
"*Parallax* is the apparent change of an observed object's position caused by "
"a shift in the observer's position. As an example, hold your hand in front "
"of you at arm's length, and observe an object on the other side of the room "
"behind your hand. Now tilt your head to your right shoulder, and your hand "
"will appear on the left side of the distant object. Tilt your head to your "
"left shoulder, and your hand will appear to shift to the right side of the "
"distant object."
msgstr ""
"*Paralaksa* je navidezna sprememba položaja opazovanega objekta, ki jo "
"povzroči premik v položaju opazovalca. Na primer, držite roko pred seboj na "
"iztegnjeni dolžini in opazujte objekt na drugi strani sobe za svojo roko. "
"Zdaj nagnite glavo na desno ramo in vaša roka se bo pojavila na levi strani "
"oddaljenega objekta. Nagnite glavo na levo ramo in zdi se, da se vaša roka "
"premakne na desno stran oddaljenega objekta."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:16
msgid ""
"Because the Earth is in orbit around the Sun, we observe the sky from a "
"constantly moving position in space. Therefore, we should expect to see an "
"*annual parallax* effect, in which the positions of nearby objects appear to "
"“wobble” back and forth in response to our motion around the Sun. This does "
"in fact happen, but the distances to even the nearest stars are so great "
"that you need to make careful observations with a telescope to detect it\\ "
"`[2] <#ftn.id11467>`__."
msgstr ""
"Ker Zemlja kroži okoli Sonca, nebo opazujemo iz nenehno spreminjajočega se "
"položaja v vesolju. Zato lahko pričakujemo učinek *letne paralakse*, pri "
"katerem se zdi, da se položaji bližnjih objektov “nihajo“ naprej in nazaj "
"kot odziv na naše gibanje okoli Sonca. To se dejansko dogaja, vendar so "
"razdalje celo do najbližjih zvezd tako velike, da morate za to opraviti "
"natančna opazovanja s teleskopom. `[2] <#ftn.id11467>`__."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:25
msgid ""
"Modern telescopes allow astronomers to use the annual parallax to measure "
"the distance to nearby stars, using triangulation. The astronomer carefully "
"measures the position of the star on two dates, spaced six months apart. The "
"nearer the star is to the Sun, the larger the apparent shift in its position "
"will be between the two dates."
msgstr ""
"Sodobni teleskopi astronomom omogočajo uporabo letne paralakse za merjenje "
"razdalje do bližnjih zvezd s pomočjo triangulacije. Astronom natančno izmeri "
"položaj zvezde na dva datuma, v razmaku šestih mesecev. Bližje ko je zvezda "
"Soncu, večji bo navidezni premik v njenem položaju med obema datumoma."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:32
msgid ""
"Over the six-month period, the Earth has moved through half its orbit around "
"the Sun; in this time its position has changed by 2 *Astronomical Units* "
"(abbreviated AU; 1 AU is the distance from the Earth to the Sun, or about "
"150 million kilometers). This sounds like a really long distance, but even "
"the nearest star to the Sun (alpha Centauri) is about 40 *trillion* "
"kilometers away. Therefore, the annual parallax is very small, typically "
"smaller than one *arcsecond*, which is only 1/3600 of one degree. A "
"convenient distance unit for nearby stars is the *parsec*, which is short "
"for \"parallax arcsecond\". One parsec is the distance a star would have if "
"its observed parallax angle was one arcsecond. It is equal to 3.26 light-"
"years, or 31 trillion kilometers\\ `[3] <#ftn.id11475>`__."
msgstr ""
"V šestih mesecih se je Zemlja premaknila skozi polovico svoje orbite okoli "
"Sonca; v tem času se je njegov položaj spremenil za 2 <firstterm>astronomski "
"enoti</firstterm> (skrajšano AU; 1 AU je razdalja od Zemlje do Sonca ali "
"približno 150 milijonov kilometrov). To se sliši kot zelo velika razdalja, "
"vendar je tudi Soncu najbližja zvezda (alfa Kentavra) oddaljena približno 40 "
"<emphasis>bilijonov</emphasis> kilometrov. Zato je letna paralaksa zelo "
"majhna, običajno manjša od ene <firstterm>ločne sekunde</firstterm>, kar je "
"le 1/3600 ene stopinje. Priročna enota za razdaljo za bližnje zvezde je "
"<firstterm>parsec</firstterm>, kar je okrajšava za \"paralaksa kotna sekunda"
"\". En parsek je razdalja, ki bi jo imela zvezda, če bi bil opazovani kot "
"paralakse ena ločna sekunda. Enako je 3,26 svetlobnih let ali 31 bilijonov "
"kilometrov<footnote><para>Astronomom je ta enota tako všeč, da zdaj "
"uporabljajo <quote>kiloparseke</quote> za merjenje razdalj na galaksijskem "
"merilu in <quote>megaparseke</quote> za merjenje medgalaktičnih razdalj, "
"čeprav so te razdalje veliko prevelike, da bi imeli dejansko, opazljivo "
"paralakso. Za določitev teh razdalj so potrebne druge metode</para></"
"footnote>.\n"
"\n"
"V šestih mesecih se je Zemlja premaknila za polovico svoje orbite okoli "
"Sonca; v tem času se je njen položaj spremenil za 2 *astronomski enoti* "
"(skrajšano AU; 1 AU je razdalja med Zemljo in Soncem oziroma približno 150 "
"milijonov kilometrov). To se sliši kot res velika razdalja, vendar je tudi "
"najbližja zvezda Soncu (alfa Kentavra) oddaljena približno 40 *bilijonov* "
"kilometrov. Zato je letna paralaksa zelo majhna, običajno manjša od ene "
"*ločne sekunde*, ki je le 1/3600 stopinje. Priročna enota za razdaljo za "
"bližnje zvezde je *parsec*, kar je okrajšava za \"parallaksa ločna sekunda"
"\". En parsec je razdalja, ki bi jo imela zvezda, če bi bil njen opazovani "
"kot paralakse ena ločna sekunda. Enak je 3,26 svetlobnih let oziroma 31 "
"bilijonov kilometrov. `[3] <#ftn.id11475>`__."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:53
msgid ""
"`[2] <#id11467>`__ The ancient Greek astronomers knew about parallax; "
"because they could not observe an annual parallax in the positions of stars, "
"they concluded that the Earth could not be in motion around the Sun. What "
"they did not realize was that the stars are millions of times further away "
"than the Sun, so the parallax effect is impossible to see with the unaided "
"eye."
msgstr ""
"`[2] <#id11467>`__ Starogrški astronomi so poznali paralakso; ker niso mogli "
"opaziti letne paralakse v položajih zvezd, so sklepali, da se Zemlja ne more "
"gibati okoli Sonca. Niso pa se zavedali, da so zvezde milijonkrat bolj "
"oddaljene od Sonca, zato učinka paralakse ni mogoče videti s prostim očesom."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-parallax.rst:64
msgid ""
"`[3] <#id11475>`__ Astronomers like this unit so much that they now use "
"“kiloparsecs” to measure galaxy-scale distances, and “Megaparsecs” to "
"measure intergalactic distances, even though these distances are much too "
"large to have an actual, observable parallax. Other methods are required to "
"determine these distances"
msgstr ""
"`[3] <#id11475>`__ Astronomom je ta enota tako všeč, da zdaj uporabljajo "
"“kiloparseke“ za merjenje razdalj v galaktični lestvici in “megaparseke“ za "
"merjenje medgalaktičnih razdalj, čeprav so te razdalje veliko prevelike, da "
"bi imele dejansko, opazno paralakso. Za določanje teh razdalj so potrebne "
"druge metode."

